						<p>Hi, I made the Guinness Mustard, then decided to riff on your recipe and make a large batch of Champagne Mustard.  I used about 2 lbs of mustard seeds (1/3 yellow, 2/3 brown), one bottle of champagne and about 4 cups of cider vinegar.  I pre-flavored the vinegar with the spices you used along with some bay, juniper, and red pepper.  It turned out delicious and these will be christmas presents this year.  Thanks for the blog and the great ideas.</p>
